    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>apple[s]</strong> finely, discard the core[s], then wash your <strong>salad </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>to a bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up, then toss through the <strong>salad</strong>, <strong>sliced apple</strong> and your <strong>walnuts </strong>and<strong> </strong>crumble your <strong>stilton cheese</strong> on top \u2013 this is your <strong>Waldorf salad</strong></p><p>Tip: You can enjoy the Waldorf salad<strong> </strong>now<strong> </strong>or set aside to have with your main course!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/3-course-waldorf-salad-nut-roast-christmas-dinner-and-figgy-pudding/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong>, then chop your <strong>flat white mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-low heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced onion</strong> (save the rest for later!) with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 5-6 min, then increase the heat to medium-high, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong> and cook for a further 5-7 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/3-course-waldorf-salad-nut-roast-christmas-dinner-and-figgy-pudding/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>While the mushrooms are cooking, peel and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-12 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once the potatoes are fork-tender, drain them in a colander and shake them until they're fluffy</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/3-course-waldorf-salad-nut-roast-christmas-dinner-and-figgy-pudding/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, roughly chop your <strong>pistachios</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>drain and rinse your<strong> green lentils</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained lentils</strong>, <strong>dried cranberries</strong>,<strong> chopped pistachios</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and your <strong>soy sauce</strong> to the onion and mushroom pan and give everything a good mix up then roughly mash \u2013 this is your <strong>pistachio</strong> <strong>nut roast mixture</strong></p><p>Line a <strong>loaf tin</strong> (or two!) with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong> and grease with <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/3-course-waldorf-salad-nut-roast-christmas-dinner-and-figgy-pudding/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pistachio</strong> <strong>nut roast</strong> <strong>mixture</strong> to the prepared tin[s], reserving the pan</p><p>Press down the mix into the corners and smooth out the top with a spatula, then put the tin in the oven for 35-40 min or until golden and firm in the middle \u2013 this is your <strong>pistachio nut roast</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop your<strong> parsnip[s]</strong> in half lengthways, then trim the ends from your<strong> Brussels sprouts</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> in quarters lengthways</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/3-course-waldorf-salad-nut-roast-christmas-dinner-and-figgy-pudding/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> to one side of a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> chopped parsnip </strong>and<strong> carrot </strong>to the other side of the tray[s]<strong> </strong>with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, add the <strong>Brussels sprouts </strong>to the tray[s] with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, return to the oven for a further 15 min or until the potatoes are crispy \u2013 these are your <strong>roast potatoes </strong>and<strong> roasted vegetables</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/3-course-waldorf-salad-nut-roast-christmas-dinner-and-figgy-pudding/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle and return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> remaining sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>to the pan with your <strong>gravy base</strong>, then cook for 7-9 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>onion</strong> <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/3-course-waldorf-salad-nut-roast-christmas-dinner-and-figgy-pudding/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Gently turn the <strong>pistachio nut roast</strong> out onto a chopping board, let it cool slightly, then cut into thick slices</p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>pistachio nut roast </strong>with the<strong> roasted vegetables </strong>and<strong> roast potatoes </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>onion</strong> <strong>gravy</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
